<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Lumbini Included in World Heritage List </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, December 7 (Xinhua) -- The World Heritage Committee
has included Lumbini, the birthplace of Lord Buddha in southern
Nepal, in the world heritage list, Nepal's official RSS news
agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
The committee made the decision at a recent meeting in Naples,
Italy, the RSS said, adding that another 45 sites were also added
into the world heritage list, bringing the number of sites in the
list to 552.
</P>
<P>
Lumbini is the second site in Nepal after the Kathmandu Valley
to be included in the world heritage list for cultural reasons,
the RSS said.
</P>
<P>
The Kathmandu Valley was included in the list in 1979.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
