<DOCNO> XIE19971208.0003 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Li Holds Talks With Senior CPV Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, December 7 (Xinhua) -- China has achieved great
achievement in recent 20 years mainly because it has correctly
understood and scientifically stuck to Maxism under the new
historical conditions, and has taken Maxism as the theoretical
basis of guiding principles, a senior Chinese official said here
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Li Ruihuan, chairman of the Chinese People's Political
Consultative Conference (CPPCC), made the remarks during his talks
with Le Kha Phieu, member of the Standing Committee of the
Communist of Vietnam (CPV).
</P>
<P>
While briefing on the recently-closed 15th National Congress of
the Communist Party of China (CPC), Li, who is also member of the
Standing Committee of the CPC Central Committee, said that a party
must have a flag, without which the party will lose its bearings.
</P>
<P>
Just as Vietnam has Maxism, Leninism and Ho Chi Minh Thought,
China has Maxism, Leninism, Mao Zedong Thought and the Theory of
Deng Xiaoping, Li said.
</P>
<P>
China has experience and lessons on how to deal with the
Maxism, Li noted, adding that after the founding of new China in
1949, great changes have taken place in China.
</P>
<P>
However, in the 20 years after 1956 when the socialism
transformation was basically completed, China has scored great
achievements, and also made serious mistakes, especially launched
the 10-year Cultural Revolution which deviated from the Maxism,
and led to disastrous consequences.
</P>
<P>
After the Cultural Revolution, China began to bring order out
of chaos by returning back to the track of Maxism, Li added.
</P>
<P>
He said that China established once again the thought of
seeking truth from facts, making clear that China is still in and
will continue to stay in the primary stage of the socialism for a
long time by adhering to materialism and criticizing idealism.
</P>
<P>
China has stuck to the view of development, opposed
conservative ideas and absorbed and learned from all beneficial
civilization fruits of the mankind, he added.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the country has also adhered to the view of
practice by taking practice as the standard of testing theory and
policy and answering and resolving problems with practice.
</P>
<P>
China has also stuck to the view of productive forces by
defining the development of productive forces as the fundamental
task of the socialism, and taking economic development as the core
of the work of the party as well as the country, Li said.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, Li continued, China has regarded the constant
improvement of people's living standard as the fundamental aim of
the reform and opening-up, and offered opportunities for people to
give full play of their talent in order to push forward the cause
with the initiative of the people.
</P>
<P>
The success of China's reform and open-up has proved that the
Maxism is not out of date, and its many basic views, especially
the materialism and historical materialism are still of
significance, he said, adding that the key is that the Maxism
should be treated in a scientific way.
</P>
<P>
Sticking to Maxism means adherence to the basic principles of
the theory rather than holding stubbornly some out-of-date words
and conclusions, or even being perplexed by some wrong views under
the name of the Maxism, Li said.
</P>
<P>
He added that adhering to the Maxism should combine theory and
reality because only in this way can the vitality of Marxism be
kept.
</P>
<P>
Deng Xiaoping's theory is a combination of the basic principles
of Maxism and China's reality, and it is the Maxism of the
contemporary China, Li said.
</P>
<P>
The 15th National Congress of CPC has defined Deng Xiaoping's
theory as the guideline of the CPC, which has been put into the
party constitution, Li said.
</P>
<P>
The theory is the basic guarantee for overcoming the
difficulties and furthering the socialist cause with Chinese
characteristics, he added.
</P>
<P>
Phieu agreed with Li, saying that both China and Vietnam's
practice has proved that the success of the socialism lies in the
combination of the basic principles of Maxism with the reality of
the countries.
</P>
<P>
He also expressed his satisfaction with the friendly
cooperative ties between the two countries and between the
Fatherland Front of Vietnam and CPPCC.
</P>
<P>
He noted that CPV and the Vietnamese people will never forget
the support of CPC and the Chinese people. The great achievements
in China's reform and open-up have encouraged Vietnam, he added.
</P>
<P>
As close neighbors, the two countries should strengthen
cooperation and exchange experience in economic development and
party organization.
</P>
<P>
He said he was confident that the historical problems between
the two countries would be properly resolved through friendly
consultations.
</P>
<P>
Li arrived here earlier in the day for a four-day goodwill
visit to Vietnam. 
</P>
</TEXT>
