<HEADLINE> Russian Party Leader Voices Support for Iraq </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BAGHDAD, December 7 (Xinhua)-- Visiting Russian Liberal
Democratic Party leader Vladimir Zhirinovsky today voiced
support for the Iraqi people in their fight against
U.S. aggression.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to reporters here, Zhirinovsky also called on "all
good powers in the world to stand against the U.S. aggression
(against Iraq)."
</P>
<P>
Iraq threatened to oust U.S. members of the U.N. weapons
inspection team last month, saying they were spying under the
cover of the U.N. mission to eliminate the country's mass
destructive weapons. Washington responded by preparing military
attack before the crisis was defused by Russian mediation.
</P>
<P>
The U.N. economic sanctions imposed after Iraqi 1990 invasion
of Kuwait will only be lifted when weapons inspectors prove that
Iraq is clear of mass destructive weapons.
</P>
<P>
Zhirinovsky said that he is carrying a letter to Iraqi
President Saddam Hussein from Russian President Boris Yeltsin
tackling bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
He arrived here Saturday evening, leading a delegation
comprising a number of parliamentary and trade figures.
</P>
<P>
During his visit to Iraq, Zhirinovsky will hold talks with
Iraqi officials to discuss means of enhancing cooperation between
Iraq and Russia in all domains. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
