<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe Police Threatens to Crush Demonstrations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, December 7 (Xinhua) -- The Zimbabwe Republic police
today has threatened to crush next Tuesday's Zimbabwe Congress of
Trade Unions (ZCTU) national mass demonstrations to protest
against the proposed five percent war veterans levy.
</P>
<P>
Police Commissioner Augustine Chihuri said the force would
without hesitation thwart any unlawful demonstrations.
</P>
<P>
"There is no point anymore to go ahead with the demonstration.
We do not want a demonstration just for the sake of a
demonstration. The people's objective has been achieved and that
decision has been reserved," he said.
</P>
<P>
"We do not want people to capitalize on other matters which
have nothing to do with the taxes. The end result of such
disorder will be chaos and we cannot tolerate that," he said.
</P>
<P>
He added that the possibilities of the planned demonstration
turning violent were very high and the police would not take
chances.
</P>
<P>
"We are appealing to those who have been mobilized that they
should forget about this demonstration. The police will not
tolerate any gatherings by people bent on bringing disorder and
causing chaos," said Chihuri. 
</P>
</TEXT>
