<HEADLINE> Mozambican Opposition Parties to Cooperate in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, December 7 (Xinhua) -- The National Resistance of
Mozambique (Renamo), the major opposition party in the country,
is to join hands with four other smaller parties in the coming
election scheduled to be held on May 29 next year.
</P>
<P>
Afonso Dhlakama, Renamo Chairman, said in central Mozambique's
Beira City that his party would cooperate with four other parties
to win over several cities in the country's first-ever regional
autonomy election.
</P>
<P>
The four parties are the United Front of Mozambique (Fumo),
the National Convention Party (PCN), the National Movement of
Mozambique (MONAMO), the Trade Union Party (PT).
</P>
<P>
Dhlakama said that this cooperation would be open to all other
parties outside of the parliament, adding that his party is
negotiating with other parties.
</P>
<P>
There are only three parties in Mozambique's parliament,
namely, the ruling Mozambican Liberation Front, the National
Resistance of Mozambique and the Democratic Union.
</P>
<P>
He said that his party would divide power with the ruling
party, admitting that his party is facing a financial difficulty.
</P>
<P>
But he said his party would take part in election in every
city and town of the country, despite all the difficulties.
</P>
<P>
According to a recent decision by the parliament, which got
the agreement from all parties, the first national election would
be held in 23 cities and 10 towns throughout the country.
</P>
</TEXT>
