<HEADLINE> Arafat Slams Israeli Breach of Peace Accords </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, December 7 (Xinhua) -- Palestinian National Authority
President Yasser Arafat today accused Israel's unilateral
activities for blocking the peace process.
</P>
<P>
"Israel has not delivered a single pledge of the signed
agreements," Arafat told reporters after a meeting with Egyptian
President Hosni Mubarak, during which he briefed Mubarak on the
outcome of his talks with U.S. Secretary of State Madeleine
Albright in Geneva Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The two leaders discussed U.S. efforts to salvage the stalled
peace process bogged down by Israel's intransigence.
</P>
<P>
Arafat arrived here Saturday night en route to Iranian capital
Tehran for the first time in more than a decade to attend the 8th
summit of the Organization of Islamic Conference due Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Israel's judaization of Jerusalem, construction of settlements,
refusal to open the airport and seaport of Gaza and the safe
passage between the West Bank and Gaza Strip have stalled the
peace process, Arafat said before leaving here for Tehran via
Qatari capital Doha.
</P>
<P>
Egyptian Presidential Political Advisor Osama el-Baz said that
Arafat expounds to Albright the Palestinian point of view and the
Palestinian demands to forge concrete progress in the situation.
</P>
<P>
Albright is pushing Israel to carry out troop withdrawal from
the West Bank and freeze Jewish settlements, said el-Baz, adding
that Albright will meet with Arafat and Israeli Prime Minister
Benjamin Netanyahu later this month to step up efforts to break
the deadlock. 
</P>
</TEXT>
