<HEADLINE> Philippine Tourism Posts Impressive Gains </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, December 8 (Xinhua) -- Despite the reported tourism
slump in the Asian region, the Philippine tourism industry has
posted significant gains during the first ten months this year.
</P>
<P>
Latest figures from the Department of Tourism showed that
tourism receipts from January to October hit 2.07 billion U.S.
dollars, a hefty 13.37 percent growth from the 1996 tourism income
recorded at 1.83 billion dollars.
</P>
<P>
In terms of tourist arrivals, the data showed that for the same
period, 1.77 million visitors came to the country and figure is
likely to increase further with the usual influx of tourism coming
to the country during the Christmas holidays.
</P>
<P>
The January-October arrivals represented a 9.72 percent
increase from arrivals for the same period in 1996 which recorded
at 1.61 million visitors, the data showed.
</P>
<P>
Visitors from the United States accounted for the major share
of 19.15 percent at 338,986, followed by Japanese tourists
registered at 305,257 or 17.24 percent of the total number.
</P>
</TEXT>
