<HEADLINE> Unemployed Double in Ukraine </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, December 8 (Xinhua) -- The number of jobless Ukrainians
reached 640,000 in the first 11 months of 1997, almost double the
figure a year ago, the State Statistics Committee said today.
</P>
<P>
However, as the official figure doesn't take into account the
laid-off workers, employment experts here estimate that 2.5 to 3
million of Ukraine's total 51 million labor force are jobless.
</P>
<P>
Over the 11-month period, the government's statistics agency
said, the State Employment Fund paid out about 20 million hryvnas
(about 10.7 million U.S. dollars) in unemployment relief.
</P>
<P>
Igor Sharov, a member of the Ukrainian parliament, urged that
urgent measures be taken to tackle the unemployment problem.
</P>
<P>
Among those most needed, Sharov said, are measures to ease the
tax burden and simplify the procedure for registering new
companies. 
</P>
</TEXT>
