<HEADLINE> Chinese Enterprise Merges Japanese Factory </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, December 8 (Xinhua) -- The Deflection Development
Corp. a subsidiary of the Shaanxi Xianyang Deflection Coil
Manufacturing Group, has merged with a Japanese machinery factory.
</P>
<P>
General Manager Du Qingsong of the group announced here today
that the corporation has invested 340 million yen to establish the
Aodai Co. Ltd. in Nagano, Japan, and merged with the Take Shita
Co. Limited.
</P>
<P>
The group, which is located in Xianyang, an industrial city in
northwest China's Shaanxi Province, is a large-scale state-owned
enterprise with subsidiaries in various sectors, including the
electronic products, automobile, machine-building and finance
sectors.
</P>
<P>
The group, China's major deflection coil manufacturer, mainly
produces components for color television tubes.
</P>
<P>
The Shaanxi Xianyang Deflection Coil Manufacturing Group has
greatly improved its competitiveness in recent years by entering
into cooperation with a number of well-known enterprises,
including Fuji, Nikon, Toshiba, Daewoo, Motorola and Kodak.
</P>
<P>
The Take Shita Co. Ltd. will mainly manufacture hardware and
precision parts.
</P>
<P>
Du said the successful merger will enable the group to
accelerate cooperation with foreign enterprises and improve its
transnational business activities. 
</P>
