Economic Cooperation of China and the Confederation of Indian
Industry.
</P>
<P>
India is China's leading trade partner in South Asia. In 1996,
bilateral trade volume between the two countries amounted to a
record high of 1.407 billion U.S. dollars, up 20.9 percent than
the previous year.  
