<HEADLINE> China Real Estate Index Issued </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 8 (Xinhua) -- Since June this year, China's
real estate sector has witnessed recovery from an extended period
of depression, according to the State Statistical Bureau.
</P>
<P>
China's Real Estate Index released here today indicates
optimistic and bright future for local developers.
</P>
<P>
The index is based on three major factors -- land, capital and
the market. It is obtained by calculating the following eight
basic reference indices: land sales, the yearly acreage for
developed land, real estate investments, investment sources, sales
of commercial housing, acreage dedicated to new buildings, acreage
for buildings under construction, and unsold commercial housing.
</P>
<P>
The index covers all annual and monthly indices for the real
estate sector since 1991. Calculations for the period between
March 1995 and October 1997 show that the index reached as high as
more than 100 points in 1995, as a result of a government funded
project to construct inexpensive housing for low-income families.
</P>
<P>
The industry has been sluggish since 1996 due to government's
efforts to curb investment in the real estate sector. Nonetheless
the index continued to rise and eventually hit 98.52 points in
October this year due to new government policies on mortgage loans
for individuals to purchase housing, interest cuts and sales of
previously unsold commercial buildings. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
