<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Market Role in Coal Production </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, December 8 (Xinhua) -- The market has long been the
major factor affecting China's coal production, and the nation's
coal producers, transporters and consumers should enhance
cooperation, Ye Qing, vice-minister of the State Planning
Commission, said at a National Coal Trade Fair in Zhengzhou today.
</P>
<P>
Ye predicted that the situation for coal production,
transportation and demand will remain stable in 1998 since the
supply and transportation capacity of the railway system can
satisfy the demands.
</P>
<P>
The vice-minister said that coal mines with better marketing
and transport conditions should increase their output, while mines
facing difficulties of selling their products due to low quality
or poor marketing capabilities should reduce production.
</P>
<P>
The coal supply for major coal users such as power plants,
fertilizer factories and coal exporters should be guaranteed
during 1998, according to Ye.
</P>
<P>
Official statistics for the first 10 months of the year show
that China produced 1.12 billion tons of raw coal, up 1.6 percent
on the previous year's period.
</P>
<P>
State-owned coal mines reduced their output to 420 million tons
in line with market requirements, down 2.7 percent on the 1996
period. The production-sales ratio of state coal producers for the
10 month period reached 100.5 percent due to readjustments. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971208.0064 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Womenlifter Sets World Record </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHIANG MAI, Thailand, December 8 (Xinhua) -- China's Meng
Xianjuan Monday lifted 117.7kg in the clean-and-jerk of the
women's 54 kg category to set a new world record at the World
Weightlifting Championships.
</P>
<P>
The 22-year-old, who is taking part in her first world
championships, beat the previous world mark of 115.5kg set by her
fellow Liu Xiuhua last July in China's Yangzhou City.
</P>
<P>
Meng also won the other two golds in the category with 87.5kg
in the snatch and 205.0kg in the overall.
</P>
<P>
Hui Ri Song from the DPR Korea took the two silvers in the
clean and jerk and the total with 110.0kg and 195.0kg respectively.
</P>
<P>
The snatch silver went to Myanmay's Knin Moe Nwe, who snatched
85kg.
</P>
<P>
China has so far claimed two world records and a junior world
record on the way to winning nine golds, five silvers and one
bronze at the current tournament started on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
China's Lan Shinzang set a new men's world record in the 54kg
clean-and-jerk category with a lift of 160.5kg Saturday.
</P>
<P>
And on Sunday, China's Yan Zhong posted a new world junior
record in the 50kg category of the snatch event. 
</P>
</TEXT>
