<HEADLINE> World's Largest Aquarium Opens in South China City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, December 8 (Xinhua) -- Guangzhou will open the
world's largest aquarium at the end of this month.
</P>
<P>
The aquarium covers an area of 12,000 sq.m. and has a floor
space of 13,400 sq. m. The facility features 15,000 marine
creatures in an artificial ecological environment.
</P>
<P>
The Guangzhou Zoo and the Leking Investment Company from Hong
Kong constructed the complex at a cost of 30 million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Visitors traversing the underwater passageway will have the
chance to view over 4,000 fish, various sharks, sting-rays
as well as dolphin performances.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the aquarium has libraries and cinemas.
</P>
<P>
An Australian company will care for all the fish in the
aquarium and US experts will supervise dolphin performances.
</P>
<P>
The aquarium will also establish a fund to help students go
abroad to study oceanography. 
</P>
</TEXT>
