<HEADLINE> Beijing Hosts Sino-Australian Consultation on Security </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 8 (Xinhua) -- Consultations with China on
security and disarmament are an important component of Australia's
dialogues with all other countries in Asia-Pacific Region.
</P>
<P>
The remarks came today from Kim Johns, deputy secretary of
Australia's Department of Foreign Affair and Trade, who is here
for the tenth round of Sino-Australian consultations on security
and disarmament.
</P>
<P>
During a meeting here today, Chinese Vice-Foreign Minister
Zhang Deguang and Kim Johns exchanged views on the security
situation in Asia-Pacific Region, multilateral security mechanisms
in the region, defense policies of the two countries and issues
concerning international military control and disarmament.
</P>
<P>
They agreed that enhancing consultations on security and
disarmament will help increase mutual understanding and
cooperation, and will lead to the further development of bilateral
relations.
</P>
<P>
China and Australia have conducted ten rounds of disarmament
consultations since 1985, with said meetings alternating between
the capitals of the two nations. 
</P>
