<HEADLINE> Shenzhen City of China Revokes Business Licenses </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, December 8 (Xinhua) -- The Shenzhen Industrial and
Commercial Administration Office has recently revoked the business
licenses of 6,748 enterprises.
</P>
<P>
This was the first time so many enterprises in Shenzhen had
been deprived of the right to conduct business because of failure
in annual examinations of business performance.
</P>
<P>
Some 2,026 of the 6,748 enterprises were foreign-funded. A
number of the said enterprises faced expiration of the
preferential tariff-free period granted by the local government.
</P>
<P>
Other companies subject to license reovations had failed to
register for bankruptcy.
</P>
<P>
Annual examinations play an important role in determining
whether an enterprise is entitled to continue economic
activities in the following year.
</P>
<P>
Enterprises failing to undergo examinations within the
prescribed period of time are subject to fines ranging between
10,000 to 100,000 yuan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
