<HEADLINE> New Railway Station for East Chinese Scenic City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, December 8 (Xinhua) -- An inauguration ceremony was
held today for building a new railway station in Hangzhou, capital
city of east China's Zhejiang Province.
</P>
<P>
Total investment for the station, which is regarded as the
largest effort for Hangzhou to renovate its old urban areas, will
reach more than 850 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
It will be rebuilt on the base of the old Hangzhoucheng
Station, with its floor space increasing to 79,000 square
meters. In front of its major structure is a 34,400 sq m
square. The new station, with a batch of advanced facilities, will
have an accommodation capacity of 5,200 people in an hour, four
times that of the old one.
</P>
<P>
A road leading to the station will be expanded to 60 meters
wide and 1,700 meters long.
</P>
<P>
Construction work is scheduled for completion by October 1, the
National Day of 1999.
</P>
<P>
Represented at today's ceremony were Cai Qinghua, Vice-Minister
of Railways, and other railway and local government
officials. 
