<HEADLINE> Senior Official Urges Trade Unions To Play Greater Role </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 8 (Xinhua) -- Wei Jianxing, member of the
Standing Committee of the Political Bureau of the Central
Committee of the Communist Party of China (CPC), today called on
trade unions at all levels to enhance understanding of the goals
and tasks set forth during the 15th CPC National Congress, and
bring the talents of workers into full play.
</P>
<P>
Wei, who also serves as president of the All-China Federation
of Trade Unions, made the remarks in a speech at the Fifth Session
of the federation's 12th Executive Committee here today.
</P>
<P>
He noted that trade union officials should arouse the
enthusiasm of workers to promote the reform and development of
state-owned enterprises and safeguard their legitimate rights in
accordance with the law.
</P>
<P>
Trade unions should pay close attention to the daily-life
difficulties faced by workers, especially laid-off workers, and
should place the reemployment of laid-off workers at top of the
agenda, according to Wei.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that trade unions should promote legislation and
the enforcement of labor laws, and should at the same time
establish and improve the mass inspection system.
</P>
<P>
He urged trade union organizations to provide workers with
instructions related to Deng Xiaoping Theory and teach them to
effectively deal with new circumstances and problems stemming from
reform and development. Wei said that trade unions should help
improve the professional skills of both laid-off and employed
workers.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out trade union should accelerate its pace of reform
to help organizations coordinate the demands of new situations by
introducing improved management and operational methods, and
should help trade union officials update their thinking and
improve their work styles.  
</P>
</TEXT>
