<BODY>
<HEADLINE> UNCP Leads in Nigeria's State Assembly Election </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, December 8 (Xinhua) -- Nigeria's state assembly
election on Saturday was again dominated by the United Nigeria
Congress Party (UNCP), the same case as in the local council poll
on March 15.
</P>
<P>
Results released so far by the National Election Commission of
Nigeria (NECON) show that the UNCP was leading in almost all the
states, winning in a total of 490 constituencies.
</P>
<P>
The Democratic Party of Nigeria came the second with 151 state
legislative seats. It was leading in Osun, Oyo and Kano states.
</P>
<P>
Three other parties lagged far behind. The National Consensus
Party was able to collected 53 seats, the Grassroots Democratic
Movement 29 and the National Center Party of Nigeria 16.
</P>
<P>
The UNCP's superority was widely expected by analysts. It
swept over 300 of the 770 local councils on March 15, far ahead
of all the four other parties.
</P>
<P>
Saturday's state assembly election was marked by an
impressively low turn-out amid a generally orderly peaceful
atmosphere.
</P>
<P>
The election is part of the military government's transition
to civil rule program. It will be followed by a national congress
election in April next year and a presidential election in
August. More results of the election are still to come. 
</P>
</TEXT>
