<HEADLINE> 15 Killed by Fire in Jakarta </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, December 8 (Xinhua) -- At least 15 people were killed
when fire engulfed the top floors of a 25-storey tower block in
Indonesia's central bank complex here this morning, said head of
Jakarta's fire brigade Suharso.
</P>
<P>
The fire started at the 24th floor of the 25-storey A tower and
was believed to have been sparked by a short circuit in the air
conditioning at 9:30 a.m., spokesman of the Central Jakarta Fire
Brigade Freddy Aling said.
</P>
<P>
Fire fighters are still evacuating the 24th and 25th floors.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the rescuers are still searching for six others who
were believed to have been trapped in the A tower's top floors,
where the fire broke out, policemen said.
</P>
<P>
Fire fighters faced difficulties reaching the top floors of the
25-storey tower but tried to prevent the fire spreading to the
floors below by spraying water on floors where the fire not yet
reached, Suharso said.
</P>
<P>
At least 25 fire engines and two helicopters operated by the
Jakarta police were deployed to extinguish the fire and evacuate
people. One helicopter was seen flying over the building several
times to pour water on the blaze.
</P>
<P>
The Indonesian central bank constructed the twin towers in
downtown Jakarta, the A tower houses the bank supervision
department. The nearby twin B tower is not yet occupied and is
undamaged.  
</P>
</TEXT>
