<HEADLINE> S. Leone Junta, Hunter Militia in Peace Talks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, December 8 (Xinhua) -- Peace talks are going on in
Sierra Leone between the military junta and traditional hunter
militias known as Kamajors loyal to former President Ahmed Tejan
Kabbah ousted in the May 25 coup.
</P>
<P>
The meeting is brokered by Nigeria, a report reaching here
said today, without giving more details.
</P>
<P>
The Kamajors have reportedly fighting against the military
government for the restoration of Kabbah's government.
