<P>
Under an earlier peace agreement, the junta agrees to step
down in April next year and all groups, including the national
army and the Kamajors, will be disarmed.
</P>
<P>
However, several negotiations between west African countries
and the junta have failed to reach consensus as the junta
insisted that the disarmament should not cover the national army.
