<HEADLINE> ASEAN Foundation to Be Set Up at ASEAN Informal Summit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, December 8 (Xinhua) -- An ASEAN foundation will
be set up during the second ASEAN informal summit in Kuala Lumpur
next week to accelerate intra-ASEAN cooperation in various fields.
</P>
<P>
A memorandum of understanding for the establishment of the
foundation will be signed by ASEAN (Association of Southeast Asian
Nations) foreign ministers in the presence of their heads of state
and government at the summit, Malaysian Foreign Ministry
Secretary-General Abdul Kadir Mohamad said today at a briefing.
</P>
<P>
Leaders of ASEAN members -- Brunei, Indonesia, Laos, Malaysia,
Myanmar, the Philippines, Singapore, Thailand and Vietnam -- will
meet for their second informal summit in the Malaysian capital on
December 14 and 15 amid the region's on-going efforts to grapple
with its economic problems which surfaced after speculative
attacks on some regional currencies.
</P>
<P>
The first ever summit between ASEAN heads of state and the
president of China as well as the prime ministers of Japan and
South Korea will be held in the afternoon of December 15, Abdul
Kadir said. He described the three countries as ASEAN's
traditional trading and investment partners.
</P>
<P>
He said the meetings come at a very important time in the sense
that the region is facing an economic setback that affects all
countries in the region.
</P>
<P>
The meetings will be an opportunity for ASEAN member countries
to discuss between themselves and then take up certain issues of
common concern with the three countries.
</P>
<P>
On the "ASEAN Plus Three" meeting, Abdul Kadir said: "I would
expect the meeting will discuss ways to re-establish confidence in
this region as ASEAN Plus Three relations are based on mutual
support and mutual prosperity."
</P>
<P>
He said ASEAN officials hoped issues such as prospects for East
Asia in the 21st century, cooperation towards regional economic
stability, preparations for the second Asia-Europe meeting in
London in April and further collaboration in the Mekong Basin
would be discussed at the "ASEAN Plus Three" meeting.
</P>
<P>
During the ASEAN informal summit, which is also known as the
ASEAN Commemorative Summit celebrating the 30th anniversary of
ASEAN, ASEAN finance ministers who met in Kuala Lumpur recently
would submit a written presentation to the ASEAN leaders on the
outcome of their meeting which helped strengthen the region's
resolve to deal with the economic setback, he said.
</P>
<P>
The foreign ministers of Indonesia, Thailand and the
Philippines who have been charged with determining ASEAN's role in
bringing back peace in Cambodia are also expected to brief the
leaders on the latest development there.
</P>
<P>
Cambodia's admission into the grouping was deferred in July at
the 30th ASEAN Ministerial Meeting due to political instability in
that country.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
