<HEADLINE> Norway Establishes Refugee Office in Kampala </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, December 8 (Xinhua) -- The Norwegian Refugee Council
(NRC) has established a refugee office in Uganda to help the
local displaced people to return home, ''The Monitor'' reported
today.
</P>
<P>
Opening the ceremony, Ugandan Minister of Labor and Social
Welfare Paul Etiang said the office is ''very welcome'' because
of the high number of internally displaced people in the northern
Gulu District in the country.
</P>
<P>
An earlier report said there are 20 refugee camps in Gulu
District to home 60,000 displaced people in the district.
</P>
<P>
Steinar Sundvoll, the NRC Regional Director, said the mission
will cooperate with local authorities to help the local displaced
people to return to their normal life. 
</P>
