<HEADLINE> Construction of Shenhua Project in Full Swing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 8 (Xinhua) -- The first project in China to
bring together the construction of coal mines, railway, power
station and port will step up energy development in the central
and western regions and energy supply for the eastern and southern
parts of the country.
</P>
<P>
In a work meeting held here recently on the construction of the
Shenhua Project, Yan Xinghua, secretary of the Chinese Communist
Party committee of Huangye City in northern China's Hebei
Province, said that the local government is giving full support to
the project.
</P>
<P>
According to Yan, the Huangye port project as a part of Shenhua
is China's largest in terms of initial investment.
</P>
<P>
To date 450 million yuan has been committed to 270 projects
since ground was broken for the port in September.
</P>
<P>
A board of directors for the port has been established. The
largest shareholder is the Shenhua Group, which is in charge of
constructing the overall project.
</P>
<P>
The group also has a holding company in charge of managing the
railway under construction.
</P>
<P>
The Shenhua Group is seeking to build a modern enterprise
system, Vice President Shi Xing of the Group said, adding that the
system will lay a solid foundation for the scheduled completion of
the project in 2005.  
</P>
</TEXT>
