<HEADLINE> World's "Longest" Noodles Made in Bangkok Chinatown </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, December 8 (Xinhua) -- Fifty cooks in Bangkok's
Chinatown last night made long noodles, which they claimed to be
the longest in the world.
</P>
<P>
The cooks spent three hours to produce the noodles which were
399 meters long. They were made from 299 kilograms of flour and
1,999 eggs. In Thailand the digit nine, which pronounces like the
Thai word for advance, is considered a lucky number.
</P>
<P>
The noodle-making was part of a program to attract tourists for
the "amazing Thailand" tourism years of 1998 and 1999.
</P>
<P>
The noodles were placed on a long table in the shape of a large
dragon along with Chinese characters wishing King Bhumibol
Adulyadej of Thailand a long life. December 5 was the king's 70th
birthday anniversary.
</P>
<P>
Yaowarat street in Chinatown is closed to traffic on the first
weekend of each month to enable residents and tourists to walk and
shop without having to worry about traffic.  
</P>
</TEXT>
