<HEADLINE> Share Prices Surge on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, December 8 (Xinhua) -- Share prices continued their
upward trend from last week and increased sharply on the Singapore
market as the benchmark Straits Times Industrials Index rose by
39.86 points to close at 1,753.63 points today.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said that the share prices were lifted by an improved
sentiment arising from Malaysia's decision to take active steps to
tackle its economic woes.
</P>
<P>
Helped by the firmer tone on the Malaysian front, Singapore
blue chips received a mild boost. Particularly, the
government-backed engineering entity Singapore Technology
Engineering, which debuted today, performed strongly, they noted.
</P>
<P>
The total market volume increased to 346.87 million units,
valued at 631.39 million Singapore dollars (about 394.62 million
US dollars). Advances overwhelmed declines by 306 to 45, while 267
other counters remained unchanged.
</P>
<P>
The Singapore Technologies Engineering was the most actively
traded counter as it registered a turnover of 38.58 million units.
It was followed by Magnum Corporation which had 20.74 million
shares traded. RHB Capital Warrant99 was next with 16.96 million
units changed hands.
</P>
<P>
Malaya Banking 200 led the gainers of the day as it rose by 1.1
dollars to end at 5.4 Singapore dollars. Malaya Banking increased
by 1.08 dollars to close at 5.4 dollars too. Uniphoenix gained one
dollar to finish at 3.4 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, JMH (Jardine Matheson Holdings) 400 was the
biggest loser as it declined by 30 cents to close at 5.15 US
dollars. Asean Fund and the Singapore Press Holdings (SPH) fell by
20 cents each to finish at nine and 16.3 Singapore dollars
respectively. JSH lost 15 cents to end at 2.75 US dollars.
</P>
