<DOCNO> XIE19971208.0129 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Roundup: Open, Fair Election of HK Deputies to NPC (by Feng Xiuju and Tao Wenge) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, December 8 (Xinhua) -- The smooth election of the 36
deputies of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (SAR) to
the Ninth National People's Congress (NPC) of China is believed to
result from the dedication of the Election Conference and the
support of the HKSAR government and people.
</P>
<P>
As is known to all, this is the first time for Hong Kong to
elect its NPC deputies as an independent constituency. In the
past, HK deputies were elected by the Guangdong Provincial
People's Congress.
</P>
<P>
The month-long election process in three stages -- the
discussion and adoption of the Detailed Election Method, the
nomination of candidates, and the preliminary and final elections
-- has been described as "open, fair and impartial."
</P>
<P>
As early as March this year, The Fifth Session of the Eighth
NPC approved the Method for Electing Deputies of the Hong Kong
Special Administrative Region (SAR) to the Ninth NPC on the basis
of views and opinions collected from among Hong Kong people.
</P>
<P>
According to the Election Method, the 36 HKSAR deputies are
elected by an Election Conference which is composed of Chinese
citizens among the members of the Selection Committee for the
first HKSAR government, and Chinese citizens among HKSAR
residents who are members of the Eighth National Committee of the
Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC) or
members of the HK Provisional Legislative Council (PLC), but are
not on the Selection Committee.
</P>
<P>
A 424-member Election Conference was formed in early November
and its members in the past month kept in close touch with people
in all walks of life, participating in various discussions on
matters related to the election. A detailed method for the
election was adopted on November 12.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Hong Kong people responded with enthusiasm.
</P>
<P>
From November 13 to 28, a total of 139 people obtained
Registration Forms for applicants for NPC deputies and 72 became
nominees with at least 10 nomination letters signed by Election
Conference members.
</P>
<P>
The Registration Office in the South Pacific Hotel received
phone calls, letters and inquiries about the election every day.
</P>
<P>
A middle school student from Sha Tin said in a letter that he
learned about the election from a local television
advertisement. He raised a number of questions about the number of
the Hong Kong NPC deputies and their functions and also about the
election of NPC deputies in Macao after it returns to the
motherland in 1999.
</P>
<P>
A taxi driver in another letter aired his views on the
requirements for the Hong Kong NPC deputies. He described the
election as a matter of great significance, saying that the NPC
deputies should be responsible for the whole of the Chinese nation
and safeguard the interest of the state wholeheartedly.
</P>
<P>
Even after the registration ended on November 28, there were
still people coming to the office to present their applications.
</P>
<P>
During the whole process of the election, a spokesman for the
Presidium of the Election Conference released news about the
election from time to time while the local media followed the
election process closely and gave a wide coverage of the event.
</P>
<P>
Local newspapers ran special columns, introducing among other
things the nominees, candidates, election procedures and the NPC
systems.
</P>
<P>
In order to ensure the smooth run of the election, a code of
conduct was imposed on the Election Conference members, which
stipulated that they are not allowed to directly or indirectly
accept bribes or seek any kind of interests from the election.
</P>
<P>
According to the Presidium spokesman, the Presidium has
received no complaints of unfairness or corrupt practice.
</P>
<P>
During the preliminary and final elections held on December 6
and 8 respectively, all Election Conference members took an
earnest, serious and responsible attitude toward the election.
</P>
<P>
Those who have been elected NPC deputies expressed their
determination to serve Hong Kong and the country as a whole.
</P>
<P>
Those who failed said they were not disappointed at the results
of the election. Some said their participation in the election was
a good beginning for their involvement in China's state affairs.
</P>
<P>
Through the election, Hong Kong people have deepened their
understanding of the people's congress system, its status and
role in China's political life. Hong Kong people will hence take
a direct part in state affairs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
