<HEADLINE> Chongqing to Promote Foreign Trade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, December 8 (Xinhua) -- Chongqing's Import and Export
Commodity Inspection Bureau has paid close attention to famous
brand products manufactured by medium and large enterprises in
order to expand the international market.
</P>
<P>
The bureau plans to regularly test major products in order to
raise quality, with related tests to be carried out on items such
as automobile parts and raw chemical materials for export.
</P>
<P>
The bureau has helped nine medium and large enterprises earn
ISO-9000 quality certifications and enhance their competitiveness.
</P>
<P>
The bureau will continue to encourage exports and promote
foreign trade, but has nonetheless ruled out a series of
preferential policies.
</P>
<P>
Joint ventures, cooperative companies and solely foreign-funded
enterprises applying for approval under the quality certification
system have the right to undergo commodity inspections.
</P>
<P>
The bureau will provide fast, effective and fair services when
foreign partners in joint ventures provide funds, or when Chinese
partners entrust them to purchase equipment and facilities.
</P>
<P>
Bureau officials noted that related measures will help
Chongqing Municipality improve its infrastructure and investment
environment. 
</P>
</TEXT>
