<HEADLINE> Almost All HK Households Visited in Voter Registration </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, December 8 (Xinhua) -- Some 30,000 Voter
Registration Ambassadors have visited nearly all the two million
households in Hong Kong during the past two days, in an all-out
effort to involve as many eligible voters as possible for the
Legislative Council polls in next May.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman for the Home Affairs Department of the Hong Kong
Special Administrative Region (SAR) said today that the results of
the weekend's unprecedented drive to register eligible voters had
amply justified (the SAR) government's determination to make the
first Legislative Council election in the SAR "a success."
</P>
<P>
"At the latest tally early this morning, the weekend's efforts
had resulted in the registration of 230,000 new voters and
collection of 60,000 forms on change of particulars," the
spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
Those households, whose residents were not at home when the
Voter Registration Ambassadors called on them in the last two
days, will be visited again in the next five days after 18:00.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman also reminded all eligible voters of registering
before the deadline on January 16.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a swearing-in ceremony of the ambassadors in Hong
Kong Park on Saturday, Chief Executive of the SAR Tung Chee Hwa
said: "This is a golden opportunity for us to show the world how
we put the concept of 'Hong Kong people ruling Hong Kong' into
practice."
</P>
<P>
To kick off the voter registration week, more than 30,000
volunteers, most of them are students of secondary schools, began
knocking at the doors of an estimated over two million households
throughout the SAR on that day. 
</P>
</TEXT>
