<HEADLINE> China's Largest Down Garment Production Base Operational </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, December 8 (Xinhua) -- China's largest down garment
production base has opened in Changshu, east China's Jiangsu
Province.
</P>
<P>
Gao Dekang, general manager of the Jiangsu-based Kangbo Group,
attended the recent Shanghai International Garment Culture
Festival. Gao noted that the group's production capacity for down
garments carrying the "Bosideng" label will double upon completion
of the second stage extension project. He said the group will
become the nation's largest producer of down garments.
</P>
<P>
Kangbo has invested 50 million yuan in the second stage
expansion project which the State Economic and Trade Commission
has listed as a key technological upgrade program. The group has
imported state-of-the-art production lines and sophisticated
technology to manufacture down garments.
</P>
<P>
The group, which sold one million "Bosideng" down garments last
winter, led the down garment manufacturing sector in sales volume
in both 1995 and 1996.
</P>
<P>
The group is not only increasing the availability of "Bosideng"
down garments on the domestic market, but is also actively
expanding its overseas markets. The group has exported products to
the United States and a number of countries in Europe. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
