<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sustainable Agricultural Development Be Ensured for 21st Century </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, December 8 (Xinhua) -- China should adopt a strategy
of sustainable agricultural development for the 21st century in
order for the sector to achieve modernization, according to
experts attending a conference on China's agricultural development
held in Changsha, capital of central China's Hunan province.
</P>
<P>
The traditional mode of agricultural production will not be
able to meet all needs of social, economic and ecological
development, according to the experts.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Farui, a professor from the China Agricultural
University, said that sustainable and intensive agricultural
development offers the only way to resolve contradictions between
the growing population and inadequate resources.
</P>
<P>
He said the strategy would allow the nation to tap the latent
potential of agriculture by raising labor productivity.
</P>
<P>
Efforts should be made to resolve acute ecological problems,
including the excessive use of farmland and groundwater, as well
as soil erosion and desertifcation, according to Wan Baorui,
vice-minister of Agriculture.
</P>
<P>
Experts said the strategy of sustainable agricultural
development will help farmers increase their income levels and
improve the rural economy.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the technology sector will play an important role
in implementing the sustainable development strategy.
</P>
<P>
China has placed priority on sustainable agricultural
development and has made agriculture the foundation for overall
economic development.
</P>
<P>
Experts estimate that the sustainable development strategy will
become the catalyst for promoting the nation's agricultural
development. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
