<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> First "Asian Tiger" Bank to Open in Tanzanian </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, December 8 (Xinhua) -- The International Bank
of Malaysia (T) Limited has become the first bank from the "Asian
Tiger" nations to be registered in Tanzania and is expected to
start operations in Dar es Salaam next year.
</P>
<P>
The Malaysian bank will open with a total capital of 3.87
million US Dollars which is more than twice the statutory minimum
capital requirement to start a bank in Tanzania, the "East
African" said today.
</P>
<P>
The bank will target the middle class and corporate clientele
and will offer both retail and corporate banking services, an
official with the bank said.
</P>
<P>
The Malaysian bank has subsidiaries in other African countries
including Conakry in Guinea and Accra in Ghana. Two more branches
are planned for the Sub-Saharan region next year.
</P>
<P>
"Malaysian fiance is seriously looking to Africa as a new area
of investment," the paper quoted the official as saying.
</P>
<P>
Since the introduction of the Banking and Financial Act of
1990, some 26 banking and financial institutions have been
licensed in Tanzania, seven of which are foreign-owned.
</P>
<P>
The sector was previously monopolized by three state-owned
commercial banks and other four financial institutions. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
