<HEADLINE> Japanese-funded Scholarship Awarded at Qinghua University </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 8 (Xinhua) -- Qinghua University, a top
Chinese institute of higher learning in Beijing, awarded "China's
Economic Research Scholarship" to 10 graduate students.
</P>
<P>
The scholarship, set up one year ago by Minoru Kobiyashi of
Japan, was awarded to 10 master's and doctoral candidates in the
Economic Management College of Qinghua University.
</P>
<P>
Kobiyashi, who worked in Japanese banking before his death,
visited China 70 times from 1979 to 1993 to give advice on China's
economic reform.
</P>
<P>
In August, 1996, his widow under conditions of Kobiyashi's
will, donated about 70 million Japanese yen (about 580,000
U.S. dollars) to establish "China's Economic Research Scholarship"
in Qinghua University and to fund economic research. 
</P>
</TEXT>
