<DOCNO> XIE19971208.0154 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Farmers Invest in Bridge Across Yellow River </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TAIYUAN, December 8 (Xinhua) -- Work on the foundation for a
highway bridge over the Yellow River has drawn wide attention
because it is being financed privately rather than by the
government, state-owned companies or foreign investors.
</P>
<P>
The bridge in Shaanxi Province, which will link the city of
Hancheng with Xiangning County, is being paid for by Li Baoping
and a group of farmers from Xiangning. Li, a Hancheng resident,
invested nine million yuan alone and other farmers contributed the
remainder.
</P>
<P>
The investors expect the bridge to transport farm and mineral
products to other parts of the country from the poverty-stricken
mountainous area.
</P>
<P>
Li, a well-known farmer-turned entrepreneur, has been involved
in coal-mining, coke-making and coal transport businesses.
</P>
<P>
Li conceived the idea to build the bridge so as to overcome the
barrier presented by the giant river to economic exchanges with
other parts of the country.
</P>
<P>
After talks with farmers on the other bank of the river, an
agreement was reached to set up a joint stock limited company to
run the bridge. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
