<HEADLINE> Guangzhou Supports Growth of High-Tech Companies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, December 8 (Xinhua) -- Construction has begun on a
non-government, high-tech park in Guangzhou, capital of southern
China's Guangdong Province.
</P>
<P>
Supported by the provincial and Guangzhou city commissions of
science and technology and the Baiyun District government, the
park covers 80 hectares in the Baiyun District. The Guangzhou
branch of the China Minsheng Banking Corp. will offer loans to
support construction.
</P>
