<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Election of HKSAR Deputies to National People's Congress Ends </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, December 8 (Xinhua) -- The Conference for Electing
Deputies of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (SAR) to
the Ninth National People's Congress (NPC) of China completed its
mission after it elected the 36 deputies today.
</P>
<P>
The 36 HKSAR deputies to the NPC were selected out of the 54
official candidates by the 424-strong Election Conference through
secret balloting at the Hong Kong Convention and Exhibition
Center this morning.
</P>
<P>
Four hundred and nineteen Election Conference members attended
the session and cast their votes today.
</P>
<P>
The Presidium of the Election Conference published the list of
the 36 deputies and will report the list to the Credentials
Commission of the Standing Committee of the NPC for approval.
</P>
<P>
Today's plenary session was chaired by Tung Chee Hwa, executive
chairman of the Presidium of the Election Conference.
</P>
<P>
The election was supervised by Chief Scrutineer Leung Chun-ying
and eight scrutineers, who are members of the Election Conference
but do not run for the NPC deputies.
</P>
<P>
The 54 official candidates were chosen from 72 nominees at the
preliminary election last Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The election of the 36 HKSAR deputies to the 9th NPC began on
November 10.
</P>
<P>
From November 10 to 12, the Election Conference elected an
11-member Presidium with Tung Chee Hwa as the executive chairman
and approved the Detailed Method for Electing HKSAR Deputies to
the Ninth NPC.
</P>
<P>
The nomination of candidates began on November 13 through
November 28.
</P>
<P>
During this period, a total of 139 people applied to run for
the 36 deputies and 72 of them became qualified nominees by
obtaining nominations from at least 10 members of the Election
Conference.
</P>
<P>
A preliminary election was held on December 6 because the
number of the nominees exceeded the number to be elected by more
than one-half. Members of the Election Conference chose 54
official candidates out of the 72 nominees.
</P>
<P>
After today's election, Tung extended his congratulations to
the 36 elected deputies on behalf of the Presidium of the Election
Conference and the HKSAR government.
</P>
<P>
He also expressed his thanks to the media which have had
extensive coverage of the election and helped Hong Kong people
learn about the whole process of the election, which is "open,
fair and impartial as anybody can see."
</P>
<P>
This is the first time for Hong Kong to elect its own deputies
to the NPC as an independent constituency since the Chinese
government resumed the exercise of sovereignty over Hong Kong on
July 1.
</P>
<P>
This is a demonstration and successful practice of the
implementation of the policy of "one country, two systems," Tung
said.
</P>
<P>
Tung vowed to support the work of the HKSAR NPC deputies and
believed that they will make contribution to the development of
the country and the prosperity and stability of Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Cao Zhi, secretary general of the Standing Committee of the
NPC, who was entrusted by the NPC Standing Committee to chair the
election, said that the whole process of this election is open,
fair and impartial.
</P>
<P>
Cao said that the media were welcomed to cover the whole
process of the election and the Presidium of the Election
Conference appointed a spokesman to communicate with the media.
These moves had helped make the election open, fair and impartial.
</P>
<P>
Through this election, the Hong Kong people deepened their
understanding of China's people's congress system and NPC's
position and role in the country's political life.
</P>
<P>
During the election, people in various circles of Hong Kong
also offered ideas and suggestions on the election of HKSAR
deputies to the NPC in future. The Standing Committee of the NPC
will ponder these ideas and suggestions seriously, he promised.
</P>
<P>
Cao expressed the hope that the newly elected deputies will
perform their duties as representatives of the Hong Kong people
and make positive contribution to the prosperity and strength of
the country and the prosperity and stability of Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Cao also announced the closing of the Election Conference.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
