<HEADLINE> 1.5 Million Overseas Tourists Visit Shanghai This Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, December 8 (Xinhua) -- China's most populous
metropolis has seen 1.5 million overseas tourists for the past 11
months of this year.
</P>
<P>
At its international airport, Shanghai authorities recently
organized a welcome ceremony for Tomio Tanaka, the 1,500,000th
traveler to the municipality.
</P>
<P>
"Our family has been here twice, and we have many friends in
Shanghai," said a cheerful Tanaka, who attended the ceremony with
his wife.
</P>
<P>
Since 1992, more than one million tourists annually have
visited Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
From January through October this year, 1.38 million overseas
travelers have come, 16 percent more than the same period last
year. In addition, tourism earned Shanghai 1.1 billion
U.S. dollars for the first 10 months of 1997, an increase of 13.8
percent compared to last year.
</P>
<P>
The eastern economic powerhouse leads other Chinese cities with
118 luxury hotels, 320 travel agencies and 194
government-designated restaurants.
</P>
