<HEADLINE> "Garden City" Honors Selected in Henan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, December 8 (Xinhua) -- Central China's Henan
Province has awarded two cities the title of "Garden City" for
excellence in greenery.
</P>
<P>
After strict expert examination and appraisal, the cities of
Puyang and Nanyang received the provincial honor.
</P>
<P>
A newly emerging oil city set up in 1984, Puyang has covered
38.2 percent of its urban area with trees, flowers and lawns.
</P>
<P>
After its elevation to city status from a prefecture in 1994,
Nanyang has devoted its efforts to becoming a garden city. The
city planted trees, flowers and lawns in 37 percent of its urban
area.
</P>
<P>
Henan has 36 cities with a combined area of 7,654 square
kilometers. 
</P>
