<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shandong to Enhance Development of Garment Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, December 8 (Xinhua) -- East China's Shandong Province,
one of the nation's leading garment production bases, has set a
goal for significantly developing the local garment industry.
</P>
<P>
Plans for the next five years call for the province to
establish an annual production capacity of three million suits,
eight million shirts, 20 million units of denim clothing, and 50
million sets of knitted underwear.
</P>
<P>
The province currently has an annual production capacity of 1.3
billion pieces of clothing, ranking fourth in the country in terms
of both clothing output and exports. The province produces 7.2
percent of the nation's total garment output.
</P>
<P>
Shandong is also home to national name brands such as "Lanyan"
clothing made of denim, "Xianxia" suits, and "Yuanshou" knitted
underwear.
</P>
<P>
The industry is preparing to introduce a series of reforms
which will emphasize the development of name brand products and
the production of high quality finished clothing. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
