<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Investor Concentrates on Taihang Mountains </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, December 8 (Xinhua) -- The first phase of an
agricultural development project in the Taihang Mountain area,
funded by a Hong Kong company, is nearly complete.
</P>
<P>
The company has invested 2 million Hong Kong dollars to
introduce more than 20 advanced tilling machines to open up 247
hectares in the first phase of a project which began in June 1996.
</P>
<P>
An experimental hothouse for breeding improved varieties of
vegetables, flowers and crops has been built at a cost of 500,000
yuan (62,500 U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
In addition, more than 20,000 apricot trees from Europe have
been planted in the newly terraced mountain slopes.
</P>
<P>
The second phase of the project will involve the development of
400 hectares. 
</P>
</TEXT>
