<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hebei Promotes Building of Unemployment Insurance System </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, December 8 (Xinhua) -- Nearly 95 percent of the
workers in north China's Hebei Province have bought unemployment
insurance policies this year.
</P>
<P>
According to the Hebei Provincial Commission for Restructuring
the Economy, workers from state, collective, joint-venture and
private ownership enterprises are all entitled to such insurance.
</P>
<P>
The state and enterprises will pay part of the insurance fee
for each worker, who pays just two yuan each year.
</P>
<P>
The unemployment insurance fund gathered in Hebei has increased
by 40 percent, hitting 210 million yuan (about 26.25 million
U.S. dollars) last year.
</P>
<P>
Hebei has provided unemployment relief funds for more than
100,000 unemployed workers from more than 40 bankrupt enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Officials said the unemployment insurance system ensures smooth
economic reforms. 
</P>
</TEXT>
