<HEADLINE> Chinese Premier Greets Opening of Islamic Conference </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 8 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Premier Li Peng, in a
message sent today to Iranian President Seyed Mohammad Khatami,
greeted the opening of the eighth summit of the Organization of
the Islamic Conference to be held tomorrow in Tehran.
</P>
<P>
"On the occasion of the opening of the Eighth Summit Meeting of
the Organization of the Islamic Conference (OIC), I wish to extend,
on behalf of the Government of the People's Republic of China and
in my own name, our warm congratulations to the Meeting," Li said
in the message.
</P>
<P>
As for the relations between China and OIC, Li Peng said "China
has maintained good relations with OIC and Islamic states and has
all along attached importance to the role of OIC in international
affairs."
</P>
<P>
"China stands ready to further enhance its friendly relations
and cooperation in various fields with Islamic states," the
Chinese premier said in the message. 
</P>
