<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0730 GMT, December 8 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG -- The 36 deputies of the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region to the Ninth National People's Congress of
China were elected here Monday.
</P>
<P>
They were selected out of the 54 official candidates, who were
chosen from 72 nominees at the preliminary election last Saturday,
by members of the 424-strong Election Conference through secret
balloting at a plenary session held this morning at the Hong Kong
Convention and Exhibition Center. Four hundred and nineteen
Election Conference members attended the session and cast their
votes Monday. (HK-NPC Deputies)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
MOSCOW -- Russia has decided to allocate 50 billion roubles
(about 8.62 million U.S. dollars) to help the suffering residents
in the Siberian city of Irkutsk, where a plane crash took place on
Saturday, killing more than 47 people.
</P>
<P>
A governmental decree made by Prime Minister Vikto
Chernomyridin, who arrived in Irkutsk to head the investigation of
the crash, said the money will be used mainly by the sufferers to
rebuild their homes. The victims included 23 people aboard the
plane, two orphans in the orphanage and 22 local residents. The
death toll is reportedly expected to rise as the rescue work goes
on. (Russia-Plane Crash-Allocation)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BELGRADE -- The Serbian Democratic Party, though leading in the
National Assembly election of the Republic of Srpska November 22
to 23, has lost its ruling party position.
</P>
<P>
Rodzer Brajant, the European Security and Cooperation
Organization representative to Banja Luka said Sunday that the
Democrat Party pulled 24 out of the 83 seats in the assembly. It
was followed by the Bosnian League for Integrity and Democracy
with 16 seats; the Srpski Narodnisavez, founded by President
Biljana Plavsic in late August, and the Serbian Radical Party,
with 15 seats each; the Serbian Socialist Party with 9 seats; and
the Serbian Independent Socialist Democratic Party and the
Socialist Democratic Party with two seats each.
(Bosnia-Serbian-Election) 
</P>
</TEXT>
