<HEADLINE> Nine-year Compulsory Education Improves Literacy Among Young </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, December 8 (Xinhua) -- East China's Anhui Province has
successfully carried out a plan for pushing nine-year compulsory
education, a program which has greatly reduced illiteracy among
the young.
</P>
<P>
Fifteen more counties this year joined the campaign to spread
basic knowledge under the program. A total of eighty-five counties
in the province have now met the goals in compulsory education.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that 98 percent of the people in the 85
counties have at least finished elementary education. More than 95
percent of the middle-school age children are enrolled in schools.
</P>
<P>
According to the provincial education commission, Anhui
Province is expected to raise the literacy rate of the young to
more than 97 percent in 1998. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
