<HEADLINE> Kenya's Inflation Rate Down to 8.2 Percent in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, December 8 (Xinhua) -- Kenya's inflation rate for
November declined to 8.2 percent from 8.7 percent in October
and 8.8 percent in September, according to a report from the
Central Bank of Kenya.
</P>
<P>
The report released by the Central bank of Kenya said that the
annual average inflation rate fell to 11.4 percent in November
from 11.7 percent in October.
</P>
<P>
The report noted that the falling inflation rate helped to
stabilize the foreign exchange market in the country.
</P>
<P>
According to a Loita Asset Management report for the week
ending November 28, the local currency Kenyan Shilling appreciated
against all the listed currencies in the week.
</P>
<P>
Turnover at the Bond Market increased marginally as bonds
worth 6.7 million U.S. Dollars were traded for the week, the
report said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
