<DOCNO> XIE19971208.0188 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 23 Kidnap Suspects Arrested in Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, December 8 (Xinhua) -- Philippine government agents
have arrested 23 suspected kidnappers in a series of raids that
started last Friday, Philippine Daily Inquirer reported today.
</P>
<P>
Agents of almost all law enforcement departments took part in
what was considered the biggest operation launched against kidnap
gangs in the past few years, the newspaper said.
</P>
<P>
The operation came on the heels of the resignation of
Philippine National Police chief Recaredo Sarmiento and President
Fidel Ramos' stern order that he wanted results in the campaign
against kidnappers.
</P>
<P>
The Filipino-Chinese community recently staged a series of
protests after two young Chinese businessmen were killed and
several others abducted by kidnappers. They appealed to the
president to stop the rampant incidence of kidnapping cases in the
country.
</P>
<P>
The suspects were members of a big syndicate tagged as the
Mindanao Group, which was responsible for more than 10 recent
kidnapping cases in Metro Manila and nearby provinces, the
newspapers said.
</P>
<P>
It added that eight of the suspected were arrested in a series
of raids on the gang's safe houses. Interrogation of them resulted
in the capture of 15 more suspects in the follow-up operations.
</P>
<P>
The Philippine government has been taking action to stop and
solve kidnappings in the country, where 950 persons have been
kidnapped and 85 of them have been killed since 1993.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
