<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Satellite TV Programs for Beijing to Go on Air </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 8 (Xinhua) -- Beijing TV will begin
broadcasting programs by satellite beginning Jan. 1.
</P>
<P>
The move will enable several billion people in China, the
Korean Peninsula, Southeast Asia, Japan, India and Mongolia to
view the station's programs.
</P>
<P>
Beijing has spent more than 800,000 U.S. dollars to launch the
project, and will pay an annual rent of an additional 800,000
U.S. dollars to use the satellite, according to the Beijing Youth
Daily.
</P>
<P>
"Quality programs will be broadcast during the 22.5-hour
operation period, mainly to provide a glimpse into local customs
and life," said Wang Hui, the station's deputy editor-in-chief.
</P>
<P>
</P>
</TEXT>
