<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Railway Passenger Traffic Increases in November </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 8 (Xinhua) -- Trains carried 2.27 million
passengers in November, an increase of 1.1 percent over the same
period last year.
</P>
<P>
The number of long-distance travelers in November was 566,000,
up 17.3 percent, according to the latest statistics from the
Ministry of Railways.
</P>
<P>
Trains carried 79,000 carloads of goods daily on average, 1,700
more than November of last year and a record for the month.
</P>
<P>
Also handled were 296,000 TEUs of containers, totaling 2.44
million tons, up more than 18 percent each.
</P>
<P>
The amount of coal transported matched last year at 33,000
carloads. Other staples including oil, iron and steel, cement,
timber, grain, fertilizer and cotton exceeded transport targets.
</P>
<P>
Railway transportation has been challenged by the booming
business on highways and by aviation. The Ministry of Railways is
meeting the competition by improving service and raising train
speeds. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
