<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Leading S. African Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, December 8 (Xinhua) -- The following are major
news items in leading South African newspapers today:
</P>
<P>
Sowetan
</P>
<P>
-- South Africa's African National Congress in Mpumalanga
Province has dropped Premier Mathews Phosa as its candidate for
the ANC national deputy presidency. Instead, it decided to throw
its support behind ANC National Chairman and Kwazulu-Natal Leader
Jacob Zuma.
</P>
<P>
The ANC Women's League, which met at the weekend to review its
earlier decision to nominate its president, Winnie
Madikizela-Mandela, as the deputy president, is believed to have
withdrawn its support for Winnie.
</P>
<P>
The Citizen
</P>
<P>
-- South Africa's Department of Correctional Services said
Sunday that investigators were working around the clock to get at
the bottom of a mass escape on Friday which saw six of South
Africa's most dangerous prisoners escape from the Pretoria Local
Prison.
</P>
<P>
-- Leaders of South Africa's ruling African National Congress
have vowed to prevent Winnie Madikizela-Mandela from becoming
party deputy president.
</P>
<P>
The Star
</P>
<P>
-- South Africa's Mpumalanga Premier Mathews Phosa has invited
former state presidents P W Botha and F W de Klerk and other
National Party leaders to witness the exhumation of African
National Congress cadres buried secretly by the apartheid
security forces. 
