<HEADLINE> CPPCC to Promote Relations With FFV: Chinese Leader </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, December 8 (Xinhua)-- The Chinese People's Political
Consultative Conference (CPPCC) will further promote its ties and
exchanges with the Fatherland Front of Vietnam (FFV), CPPCC
National Committee Chairman Li Ruihuan said here today.
</P>
<P>
During his meeting with FFV Chairman Le Quang Dao, Li expressed
his satisfaction with the development of the relations between
CPPCC and FFV, saying that recent years have witnessed close
relations and enhanced exchanges between the two organizations,
which has played a positive roles in cementing the mutual
understanding and trust between the peoples of two countries.
</P>
<P>
Li, who arrived here Sunday for a four-day goodwill visit,
cited the CPPCC and FFV as political organizations with
characteristics of united front, which have special status and
functions in the political life of both countries.
</P>
<P>
"We hold that the development of friendly relations between
countries should be extensively carried out on various levels,
through different channels and by various sectors," Li said.
</P>
<P>
"Only in this way can the bilateral relations be strengthened,"
he added.
</P>
<P>
Dao said that Li's visit will not only help enhance the
relations between the two organizations, but will also spur the
ties between the two countries and two communist parties.
</P>
<P>
He hoped that the two organizations will further promote their
relations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
