<HEADLINE> Thirty-six HKSAR Deputies to China's Ninth National People's Congress Elected </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, December 8 (Xinhua) -- The 36 deputies of the Hong
Kong Special Administrative Region (SAR) to the Ninth National
People's Congress (NPC) of China were elected here today.
</P>
<P>
They were selected out of the 54 official candidates by members
of the 424-strong Election Conference through secret balloting at
a plenary session held this morning at the Hong Kong Convention
and Exhibition Center.
</P>
<P>
Tung Chee Hwa chaired the plenary session as executive chairman
of the Presidium of the Election Conference.
</P>
<P>
The 54 official candidates were chosen from 72 nominees at the
preliminary election last Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Four hundred and nineteen Election Conference members attended
the session and cast their votes today.
</P>
<P>
Today's election was supervised by Chief Scrutineer Leung
Chun-ying and eight scrutineers, who are members of the Election
Conference but do not run for the NPC deputies.
</P>
<P>
The list of the 36 deputies will be reported to the Credentials
Commission of the Standing Committee of the NPC for approval.
</P>
</TEXT>
