<TEXT>
<P>
Wellington, December 8 (Xinhua) -- The New Zealand sharemarket
showed strength today, with the main market indicator finishing
higher despite dividends worth about 17 points on the NZSE40
Index.
</P>
<P>
The NZSE40 Index ended 8 points higher at 2,402 with a turnover
of 64 million dollars (38 million US dollars).
</P>
<P>
Among the stronger leaders, Air New Zealand rose 3 cents to 243
cents, Brierley Investment gained 1c to 123c, Carter Holt Harvey
rose 5c to 260c, Fletcher Building jumped 15c to 460c, and
Fletcher Energy climbed 7c to 662c.
</P>
<P>
On the weaker side, Lion Nathan fell 3c to 385c. But Telecom
ended unchanged at 890c.
</P>
<P>
Overall, there were 54 rise and 27 falls.  
