<HEADLINE> Vietnam Grants Licenses to 279 Foreign-Invested Projects </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, December 8 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam has granted licenses in
the first 11 months of this year to 279 foreign-invested projects
with a total capital of nearly 4 billion U.S dollars, local media
reported here today.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam's Ministry of Planning and Investment was quoted as
saying that about 1.6 billion dollars were invested in industrial
sector, 107 million in oil and gas, 762 million in transportation
and communications, 366.3 million in architecture, 67.2 million in
agriculture, forestry and fishery.
</P>
<P>
Ho Chi Minh city took the lead in attracting foreign investment
with 43 projects worth 788 million dollars, followed by Hanoi with
32 projects worth 726 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
So far, the Republic of Korea is the biggest investor in
Vietnam with a total investment capital of 654.3 million
dollars. Japan ranks the second with 545.5 million dollars,
followed by France with 535 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
Of the 4 billion-dollar foreign investment, the realized
capital stood at 2.7 billion dollars, 39 percent higher than last
year.
</P>
<P>
Since early 1988, there have been 1,777 foreign-invested
projects with a combined capital of 31.2 billion dollars operating
in Vietnam. 
</P>
</TEXT>
