<HEADLINE> Bangladeshi PM Calls on Political Parties to Help </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, December 8 (Xinhua) -- Bangladeshi Prime Minister Sheikh
Hasina has call on political parties to extend full cooperation in
implementing the peace accord to end the decades-old insurgency in
the Chittagong Hill Tracts (CHT) region.
</P>
<P>
The prime minister made the call while exchanging views with
newsmen at her official residence Sunday.
</P>
<P>
She asserted that the implementation of the agreement would
ensure human rights and establish "unity in diversity" in the
trouble-torn CHT region.
</P>
<P>
The agreement signed on December 2 between the government and
the tribal leaders has been hailed by the international community
including the United States, Australia, the United Kingdom,
France, the Netherlands and Pakistan, she told newsmen.
</P>
<P>
Expressing her government's appreciation for the support
extended within and outside the country, she believed that the
peace agreement had not only enhanced the country's image but also
paved the road to national development through peace and harmony.
</P>
<P>
She called upon the opposition to shun the false and baseless
propaganda aimed at misleading the people.
</P>
<P>
She observed that only arms smugglers and the vested interest
group opposed peace in three hill districts that constituted one
tenth of the country's total area.
</P>
<P>
The copy of the agreement was already submitted to the
president after it was signed, she said, adding that her
government wants discussion on the peace agreement in parliament.
 
</P>
</TEXT>
