<HEADLINE> Myanmar Stresses Implementation of Low-Cost Housing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, December 8 (Xinhua) -- Myanmar Leader Khin Nyunt has
stressed the need to implement low-cost housing projects for the
public and service personnel.
</P>
<P>
While meeting with housing project officials here Sunday, Khin
Nyunt, first secretary of the Myanmar State Peace and Development
Council, said every nation needs construction activities according
to its size, pointing out that there should be no over-building
that exceeds the requirement, official daily The New Light of
Myanmar reported today.
</P>
<P>
Khin Nyunt, who is also chairman of the Myanmar Privatization
Commission and chairman of the Housing Project Committee, spoke of
taking lessons of construction entrepreneurs who suffered loss in
some countries due to lack of systematic project appraisals.
</P>
<P>
Myanmar has drawn up new housing projects in the capital of
Yangon to move more residents from huts to apartment buildings due
to considerable population growth in Yangon.
</P>
<P>
The population in the capital has exceeded 5 million living in
35 townships, according to official statistics.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, more and more residents have been relocated to
several new towns near Yangon as old huts and buildings have been
demolished or reconstructed to give the capital a more urban look.
</P>
<P>
</P>
