<DOCNO> XIE19971208.0229 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Zoo Boosts Rare Animal Reproduction </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 8 (Xinhua) -- Beijing Zoo, China's largest
treasure house of animals and birds, has made marked progress in
the reproduction of rare animals.
</P>
<P>
The zoo said keepers have bred 1,530 animals from 104 species
in the first 10 months of this year.
</P>
<P>
The American buffalo, which has not been bred in the zoo for 27
years, was successfully reproduced this year, reported today's
China Daily.
</P>
<P>
The number of species and animals and the high survival rate
were all records, one zoo official said.
</P>
<P>
The offspring of rare and valuable animals will be exhibited to
visitors next year.
</P>
<P>
The zoo currently houses more than 3,000 animals from more than
600 species.  
</P>
</TEXT>
