<HEADLINE> Nation to Test Electric Vehicles </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 8 (Xinhua) -- Increasingly intensified
pressure in the areas of oil supply and environmental protection
is prodding China to seek a special strategy to boost the
development of the automotive industry.
</P>
<P>
Japan's Toyota Motor Co will supply five 5-door "RAV4" electric
vehicles to a pilot program of electric vehicles, slated to kick
off in Spring of 1998 at Nan'ao Island off Shantou in Guangdong
Province, today's "China Daily" reports.
</P>
<P>
"We are exploring the possibility of popularizing the use of
electric vehicles throughout the country," said Zhang Zhiwen, a
division chief with the department of industrial technology under
the State Science and Technology Commission (SCTC).
</P>
<P>
The electric vehicle pilot program, which was jointly initiated
by the State Planning Commission, the SCTC, Ministry of
Machine-Building Industry, and Guangdong Province, is aimed at
providing testing data and accumulating experience necessary for
the building of service facilities, market promotion, as well as
implementing industrial policies and related traffic laws.
</P>
