<HEADLINE> Albania's Economy Slightly Better Than Expected </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, December 7 (Xinhua) -- Though still in trouble,
Albania's current economic situation turns out to be better than
expected, Albanian government spokesman told reporters Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Ben Blush said as a result of the government's efforts, the
country's current Gross National Product (GNP) decreased by 7
percent, less than the expected 8.5 percent.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the inflation rate and budget deficit are 40
percent, and 12 percent respectively, less than the 50 percent and
15 percent as projected.
</P>
<P>
Earlier this year, Albania was plunged into economic crisis
following wide-spread turmoil resulting from the fraudulent saving
schemes. 
</P>
</TEXT>
