<HEADLINE> Cruz Azul Wins First Mexican Title in 17 Years </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, December 7 (Xinhua) -- Cruz Azul won the Mexican
league soccer title for the first time in 17 years on Sunday after
beating Leon with a sudden-death "golden goal" penalty in
extra-time in Leon on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Substitute Carlos Hermosillo, Mexico's all-time top scorer,
converted the penalty to give the Mexico City side a 1-1 second
leg draw and 2-1 aggregate win.
</P>
<P>
Cruz Azul had won the first leg of the final 1-0 at home but
were forced into extra time after Missael Espinosa scored for Leon
in the 51st minute.
</P>
<P>
As top team in Mexican soccer, Cruz Azul last won the national
title in the 1979-80 season, having come close frequently and lost
in the 1994 finals. 
</P>
</TEXT>
