<HEADLINE> HK Election Conference Selects Deputies to China's National People's Congress </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, December 8 (Xinhua) -- Members of the Conference for
Electing Deputies of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region
(SAR) to the Ninth National People's Congress (NPC) of China began
to select 36 deputies here this morning.
</P>
<P>
The 36 are selected through secret balloting out of the 54
official candidates who were determined by the 424-strong Election
Conference by vote last Saturday.
</P>
<P>
This is the first time for Hong Kong to elect its own NPC
deputies as an independent constituency since it returned to China
on July 1 this year.
</P>
<P>
A list of the 36 elected deputies will be published by the
Presidium of the Election Conference later today and then reported
to the Credentials Commission of the Standing Committee of the
NPC.
</P>
<P>
If approved, they will become the first group of deputies of
the HKSAR to the NPC with a term of five years. 
</P>
