<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Brazil Beats South Africa 2-1 in Soccer Exhibition </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, December 7 (Xinhua) -- Romario and Bebeto both
scored in the first half to lead world champion Brazil to a 2-1
win over South Africa in an exhibition soccer match here on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Both sides have qualified for the 1998 France World Cup finals
but the hosts was no match for Brazil's quickness and
ball-handling wizardry.
</P>
<P>
The South Africans had few serious scoring chances but they
really caught one on a 78th minute goal from substitute Helman
Mkhalele to cut the gab at 2-1.
</P>
<P>
South Africa qualified for the World Cup finals for the first
time since it returned to international soccer in 1992 after being
banned two decades because of apartheid.
</P>
<P>
Despite a strong record in Africa, including its African
Nations Cup triumph in 1995, South Africa has yet to defeat a
legitimate European or South American power in the past two years,
including two losses to Brazil and defeats by England, France,
Germany and the Netherlands. 
</P>
</TEXT>
