<HEADLINE> NZ's New Prime Minister Sworn In </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, December 8 (Xinhua) -- Jenny Shipley was sworn in
at the Government House this morning to become the new prime
minister of New Zealand.
</P>
<P>
She is the first woman prime minister in New Zealand's history.
</P>
<P>
Shortly before the swearing-in ceremony presided by Governor
General Michael Hardie Boys, outgoing prime minister Jim Bolger
tendered his resignation to the governor general.
</P>
<P>
Extending his congratulations to Shipley, Sir Michael Hardie
Boys said, "It is a very special occasion, of course, for the
nation, particularly because you are the first women prime
minister."
</P>
<P>
After Shipley and her new cabinet were sworn in, they had their
first meeting under Shipley. On the agenda was a proposal to
reform the way of funding and managing NZ's roads.
</P>
<P>
It is reported that new measures under consideration include
road tolls for motorists.  
</P>
</TEXT>
