<HEADLINE> Half Ton Cocaine Seized in US </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, December 7 (Xinhua) -- Two men are arrested and 480
kilograms of cocaine with a street value of 60 million US dollars
were seized by law enforcement agencies in Texas Friday night.
</P>
<P>
The men were arrested after police got an anonymous tip about a
suspicious tractor-trailer rig. Fort Worth investigators today are
working with the federal Drug Enforcement Administration to trace
the origin of the drug shipment, the United Press International
said.
</P>
<P>
The arrested were Luis Betancourt of Pasadena and Rosendo
Morales of La Porte. They were facing drug charges in the case.
</P>
<P>
Two weeks ago, officers seized 56 kilograms of cocaine after
making a routine traffic stop. 
