<BODY>
<HEADLINE> UK Nurses Face Most Violence at Work </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, December 7 (Xinhua) -- Nursing in Britain is currently
the most dangerous profession, with 34 percent of nurses having
been attacked while doing their jobs, five times more likely than
the average worker to be the victims of such violence.
</P>
<P>
Citing a latest research by the Health and Safety Executive,
local press reports today said that security and protective
services workers, including police officers and doormen, are less
vulnerable, with 25 percent of workers being attacked.
</P>
<P>
Then come social and care workers, with 21 percent, and
teachers and other education staff, with 14 percent.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the possibility of being threatened with violence is
now commonplace in many workplaces in the country. Once again,
nurses are most at risk, with 48 percent saying they have been
threatened.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that Chairman of the Health and Safety
Commission Frank Davies will next week present Health Secretary
Frank Dobson with new plans for counteracting the tide of violence
against health professionals. 
</P>
</TEXT>
