<HEADLINE> Islamic World Awakened: Iranian Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, December 7 (Xinhua) -- Iranian Foreign Minister Kamal
Kharrazi stated today that the forthcoming Islamic summit will
tell the enemies that the Islamic world is awakened.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a press conference here, Kharrazi said the Islamic
world is keeping pace with global changes and will play an
important role in the future world.
</P>
<P>
The summit of the Organization of Islamic Conference (OIC) to
be held here December 9-11 will also help improve mutual
understanding, unity and cooperation among the Islamic countries,
he said.
</P>
<P>
He made the remarks following the conclusion of the OIC foreign
ministers' meeting which endorsed more than 140 draft resolutions.
</P>
<P>
The minister said that in order to brush up the OIC functions,
a group comprising OIC previous, present and future presidents
will look into the OIC structural and financial reforms.
</P>
<P>
The Iranian official dismissed the claims that Iran has not
taken concrete steps to improve its relations with the Arab
world, saying that Iran always tries to remove misunderstandings
and expand friendly relations with the Arab world.
</P>
<P>
In the context of the latest development in the region,
particularly the deadlock of the Middle East peace process,
Kharrazi said, a suitable circumstance has been created for Iran
to promote its relations with its neighbors.
</P>
<P>
He praised the Iraqi government for releasing two Iranian
nationals recently, saying that Baghdad's decision has indicated
its willingness to improve relations with Iran.
</P>
<P>
The Iranian foreign minister also voiced Iran's readiness to
solve remaining problems between the two neighbors, particularly
the issue of prisoners of war.
</P>
<P>
However, he reiterated that Tehran opposed recognition of the
Israeli identity and the establishment of ties between some
Islamic countries and the Jewish state, adding that Iran would
not establish any ties with Israel due to its aggressive nature.
</P>
</TEXT>
